  <roomsDescription><![CDATA[<p><strong>Standard rooms</strong> are around 18m² and are comfortable rooms for two people. These are the smallest rooms and not all have a balcony. They are also available for sole use with a supplement, please call us to book this room type. </p>
<p><strong>Comfort rooms</strong> are 19m² and are located in the west wing of the hotel. They all have a bathroom with walk-in high pressure rain forest-style shower and balcony with views of the slopes or the Méribel valley.</p>
<p><strong>Prestige rooms</strong> are around 22m² located in the East wing of the hotel and can sleep two to three. Each room has a balcony, floor to ceiling window and stunning views of the slopes.</p>
<p><strong>Prestige triple rooms</strong> are 22m² and can sleep three. These rooms have three single beds or a king size and single bed. All rooms have a balcony with views of the slopes.</p>
<p><strong>Prestige quad rooms</strong> are 34m² and can sleep four. The room have a king size bed or two single beds and additional bunk beds or sofa beds. These rooms feature a  balcony and high pressure shower.</p>
<p>Some prestige rooms have interconnecting doors. Please call to request if required.</p>
<p><strong>Accommodation Facilities</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Double or twin beds (please specify preference when booking)</li>
<li>Views of the slopes or the mountain valley</li>
<li>Shower and WC</li>
<li>Wi-Fi access</li>
<li>Satellite TV </li>
<li>Daily house keeping </li>
<li>Safe</li>
<li>Hairdryer</li>
</ul>
<p> </p>
<p> </p>]]></roomsDescription>
